[\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2023 Women's Boxing World Championships\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 908}, {\"ngram\": \"both Lin\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 918}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 929}, {\"ngram\": \"their medals\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 959}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two had failed an unspecified gender eligibility test, according toAP News.\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an unspecified gender eligibility test\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1064}, {\"ngram\": \"toAP News\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1085}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This typically happens when the test detects elevated levels of testosterone in a female athlete.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the test\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1123}, {\"ngram\": \"elevated levels\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1147}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1163}, {\"ngram\": \"a female athlete\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around the time that the two were disqualified, IBA president Umar Kremlev said: \\\"Based on DNA tests, we identified a number of athletes who tried to trick their colleagues into posing as women.\\\"\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1234, \"end\": 1237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.7364465172569202, \"rank\": 0.33898016310121665, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\", \"score\": 0.9999975978557106, \"rank\": 2.394987777416829e-06, \"text\": \"Umar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1201}, {\"ngram\": \"DNA tests\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1286}, {\"ngram\": \"a number\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1322}, {\"ngram\": \"their colleagues\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1358}, {\"ngram\": \"posing\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1370}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1379}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet, he did not specify if he was referring to Khelif, Lin Yu-Ting, or other fighters.\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1437, \"end\": 1448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-Ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1435}, {\"ngram\": \"other fighters\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally,Yahoo Newsreported that: \\\"Yu-Ting and Khelif are not transgender, they were born female, but tests show that their DNA contains the usually male-associated XY chromosomes, rather than usually female-associated XX chromosomes, meaning their testosterone levels are more akin to that of a man's, who can punch up to 2.6 times harder than a woman.\\\"\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1693, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 0.9999999999465672, \"rank\": 5.335554917070539e-11, \"text\": \"XX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Additionally,Yahoo Newsreported\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1501}, {\"ngram\": \"Yu-Ting\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"tests\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1581}, {\"ngram\": \"their DNA\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1601}, {\"ngram\": \"the usually male-associated XY chromosomes\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"their testosterone levels\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1742}, {\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1773}, {\"ngram\": \"a woman\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IBA has since not been recognized by the International Olympic Committee (IOC), who allowed Lin and Khelif to compete in the 2024 Olympic games.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1978, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.7364465172569202, \"rank\": 0.33898016310121665, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 1875, \"end\": 1912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1929}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1940}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic games\", \"from\": 1955, \"to\": 1977}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These two athletes were the victims of a sudden and arbitrary decision by the IBA,\\\" The IOC stated.\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 2080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2059,